Victory ! ? (Nami) It's impossible, it's impossible.

503
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:45,000
You won't know until you try. (Yuzuki) Are you going to tell me the truth?

504
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:47,000
(Kurose) Oh? (Kurose/Yuzuki) Hello.

505
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:51,000
So please hurry up and bring all the materials for your presentation.

506
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:54,000
Eh! ? (Nagisa) I'm so tired.

507
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:06,000
The judges don't want to be impressed.

508
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:09,000
Look at data and numbers.

509
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:11,000
That's why you guys did such amazing things➡

510
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,000
We have to show our track record.

511
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:18,000
For example, the amount of damage caused by jellyfish on the coast of Wakasa Bay➡

512
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:22,000
such as protein content. (Yuzuki) Muzu.

513
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:27,000
Well, I'll try making it anyway. Yeah .

514
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:30,000
(Yuzuki) Yes. (Nami) Yes.

515
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:33,000
(Yuzuki) Please. (Nami) Nice to meet you.

516
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:37,000
(typing sound)

517
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:50,000
♬～

518
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:55,000
We extract collagen from large jellyfish➡

519
00:38:55,000 --> 00:39:00,000
We developed tofu as a new value-added food.

520
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:04,000
(Nagisa) This research aims to effectively utilize local resources and ➡

521
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:07,000
The purpose is to reduce the burden on fishermen.

522
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:12,000
(Yuzuki) We can also expect economic effects from branding.

523
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:16,000
(applause)

524
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:21,000
Well done, Mr. Asano. Well done.

525
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:23,000
The students did a great job.

526
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:25,000
(Kurose) Don't be so humble➡

527
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:28,000
The teacher must have rewritten all the materials. ➡

528
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:30,000
That was perfect. ➡

529
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:35,000
The students invented it, but the teacher took credit for winning. ➡

530
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:38,000
I'm sure the students understand that too.

531
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:54,000
(Nami) “In our sea➡

532
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:58,000
There is a jellyfish that is called a nuisance.'' ➡

533
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:02,000
`` No one has expectations and no one hits the market ➡

534
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:05,000
It has been labeled as useless.” ➡

535
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:10,000
``There is no destination, just being carried away by the ocean current➡

536
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:13,000
Just swimming around the place➡

537
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:15,000
Troublesome jellyfish” ➡

538
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:17,000
``I feel like that➡

539
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:20,000
I thought it was just like us.”

540
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:31,000
(Nami) “There’s no way I can be the main character in the ocean➡

541
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:34,000
I don't have anything special.'' ➡

542
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:37,000
"One of many others"

543
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:45,000
(Nami) “But the truth is, there are things that only we can do.” ➡

544
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:49,000
``Even if you're a nuisance that no one expects from you➡

545
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:52,000
It must be worth it.” ➡

546
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:55,000
"We wanted to prove it."

547
00:40:57,000 --> 00:41:02,000
(Nami) “That’s why I invented this jellyfish tofu.”

548
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:21,000
♬～

549
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:27,000
What should I do if I destroy the students' thoughts?

550
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:43,000
(Kijima) Certification standards? (East Exit) Major food manufacturers are now ➡

551
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,000
We're starting to get into space food.

552
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:48,000
We have to set the standards.

553
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:51,333
Do you know HACCP? (Kijima) Hassap?

554
00:41:51,333 --> 00:41:55,000
Don't you even know that? (Yuzuki) What? What is Hamap?

555
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:58,000
(Ryūku) Hassap na. (Yuzuki) I don't understand English.

556
00:41:58,000 --> 00:42:00,000
(Ryūku) It's in the textbook.

557
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:04,000
The food hygiene management system that NASA devised to produce space food.

558
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:07,000
NASA is that NASA? Are you going to explore space?

559
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:09,000
There's nothing else like it.

560
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:12,666
ＮＡＳＡ ？

561
00:42:12,666 --> 00:42:17,000
(East Exit) Yes, it is a food hygiene management system created by NASA. ➡

562
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:20,000
It is essential for future food hygiene management. ➡

563
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:22,000
The space environment is harsh. ➡

564
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:27,000
We need to aim for HACCP or higher.

565
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,000
(Nagisa) Then we need to get that HACCP➡

566
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:32,000
Does that mean the jellyfish tofu we made can't be commercialized?

567
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:35,000
(Ryūku) Yes, from now on, we won't be able to do anything without that HACCP.

568
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:39,000
If you do it, you should take it now.

569
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:42,000
(Ryūku) Huh? It's an impossible game right now. ➡

570
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:45,000
Don't take HACCP lightly. (Yuzuki) Certainly. ➡

571
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:49,000
It was made by NASA, the space agency. ➡

572
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:53,000
Isn't it impossible for us? (Nagisa) It's just impossible.

573
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:56,000
There's no point in just doing it.

574
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:59,000
Try it, you won't understand.

575
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:02,000
(Ryūku) No, no, I understand. (Nami) I don't understand.

576
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:07,000
Let's try it. You can even make jellyfish tofu!

577
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:11,000
That's right. (Yuzuki) Should I try it?

578
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:19,000
That's amazing. Oh, teacher.

579
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:24,000
He's way ahead of me.

580
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:26,000
(Yuzuki) What is that?

581
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:33,000
Um... can I join in too?

582
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:36,000
It's obvious. What should I do if my teacher is missing?

583
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:39,000
(Ryūku) No, that's why it's impossible to get HACCP easily.

584
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:43,000
Does that mean we can make space food at home if we take that?

585
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:48,000
Well, if you get HACCP, yes.

586
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:54,000
If we did that, wouldn't we be able to send our mackerel cans into space?

587
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:03,000
No compromises are necessary. Shauninuni.

588
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:06,000
It's Kijima-kun's turn.

589
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:09,000
(Kijima) It is true that the space environment is harsh.

590
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:11,000
One microorganism or one piece of debris can lead to an accident.

591
00:44:11,000 --> 00:44:14,000
Failure is not an option. (East exit) Yes.

592
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:19,000
(Kijima) I will create a new standard for space food.

593
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:24,000
Sending our canned mackerel to space.

594
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:29,000
[At that time, no one knew about it]

595
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:33,000
[With high school students from this small port town➡

596
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:37,000
A new teacher who came from outside...]

597
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:45,000
Thank you for waiting.

598
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:49,000
Oh, I don't have chopsticks. You can use your hands, right? You can use your hands...

599
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:58,000
Thank you for your hard work.

600
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:04,000
[With the adults who live here➡

601
00:45:04,000 --> 00:45:09,000
With the support of adults watching over the universe➡

602
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:11,000
Eventually it will be true➡

603
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:18,000
Canned mackerel made by high school students will be sent into space]

604
00:45:18,000 --> 00:45:25,000
[It all started with a dream of just one word]

605
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:13,000
[“Canned Mackerel Goes to Space”]
